<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ronin_(DC_Comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Film adaptation">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Film_adaptation">Film adaptation</span></h2>
<p>In 1998 <a href="Darren_Aronofsky" title="Darren Aronofsky">Darren Aronofsky</a> inked a deal with <a href="New_Line_Cinema" title="New Line Cinema">New Line Cinema</a> for a film adaptation of the graphic novel.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> In 2007 Gianni Nunnari, producer of <i><a href="300_(film)" title="300 (film)">300</a></i>, announced he would be producing and <a href="Sylvain_White" title="Sylvain White">Sylvain White</a>, director of <i><a href="Stomp_The_Yard" title="Stomp The Yard" class="mw-redirect">Stomp The Yard</a></i>, directing the <i>Ronin</i> film adaptation.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ronin_(DC_Comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Influence">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Influence">Influence</span></h2>
<p>Animation director <a href="Genndy_Tartakovsky" title="Genndy Tartakovsky">Genndy Tartakovsky</a> has noted that <i>Ronin</i> was one of the major influences on his animated TV series <i><a href="Samurai_Jack" title="Samurai Jack">Samurai Jack</a></i>.<sup class="Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources from May 2011">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ronin_(DC_Comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
